# Audit records

For any durable, auditable body an LLM agent authors — git commit, PR description,
Jira comment, incident note, change record — make authorship and rationale explicit.

## Attribution & rationale

- State agent authorship via an `Authored-By` trailer naming the harness and its version.
- Include a concise summary explaining each material change and WHY.
- If materially changing a Jira ticket's saved fields (title, description, acceptance
  criteria, scope, status), add a Jira comment recording each change + rationale.

## Commit authorship

The human remains commit author and committer. Append an `Authored-By` trailer to every
agent-authored commit with the verified harness name and version. Never emit a
`Co-Authored-By` trailer.

## Runtime provenance block (keep it greppable)

Use this authoritative field order:

1. `Authored-By`
2. `Model`
3. `Model-Provider`
4. `Model-Gateway` — conditional: emit only when the model is routed through a
   gateway/proxy; omit the line entirely for direct providers.
5. `Session-ID`
6. `Hostname`

For harnesses without a runtime metadata tool, record each value's source inline — e.g.
`Model: claude-opus-4-8 (source: session)`. Terse source labels: `session` for live
runtime values; the applied config filename (e.g. `~/.codex/config.toml`) for config
values.

## Resolution order (per attribute)

1. Current live session / runtime context (incl. status/UI metadata).
2. Active applied config — NOT repo templates or dotfile source.

Never assume or guess a metadata value — if it cannot be dynamically read from a source
of truth, default to `unknown (source: unavailable)`. Copy values exactly as shown — never
infer from API base URLs, proxies, or assumed vendors.
